PREAMBLE

Dome Pro is an open-source project created with the goal of building a 
powerful knowledge management tool through community collaboration. We 
believe in the power of open source and welcome contributions from everyone.

This license allows you to use, modify, and contribute to Dome Pro while 
ensuring the project remains sustainable and community-focused.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DEFINITIONS

"Software" refers to Dome Pro and all associated source code, documentation,
and assets contained in the official repository.

"Official Repository" refers to the main Dome Pro repository maintained by
the original author(s). This is the authoritative source for the Software.

"Commercial Use" means any use of the Software intended for or directed toward
commercial advantage or monetary compensation. This includes, but is not
limited to: selling the Software, using the Software to provide paid services,
incorporating the Software into a commercial product, or using the Software
in a business context that generates revenue.

"Personal Use" means use by an individual for personal projects, learning,
research, or non-commercial purposes.

"Educational Use" means use by educational institutions, students, or 
educators for teaching, learning, or academic research purposes.

"Contribution" means any work of authorship submitted to the Official 
Repository, including modifications, additions, or improvements to the 
Software.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GRANT OF RIGHTS

Subject to the terms and conditions of this License, you are granted the 
following rights:

1. PERSONAL AND EDUCATIONAL USE

   You may use, copy, modify, and run the Software for personal and 
   educational purposes without restriction.

2. CONTRIBUTION RIGHTS

   You are encouraged to contribute to the Software by:
   - Reporting bugs and issues
   - Submitting feature requests
   - Contributing code improvements
   - Improving documentation
   - Helping other users in the community

   By submitting a Contribution, you grant the project maintainers a 
   perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use, 
   reproduce, modify, and distribute your Contribution as part of the 
   Software.

3. FORK RIGHTS

   You may fork the Official Repository for the purpose of:
   - Developing contributions to submit back to the Official Repository
   - Personal experimentation and learning
   - Academic study and research

   However, maintaining a separate public fork as an alternative to the 
   Official Repository is discouraged. We encourage all improvements to 
   be contributed back to the main project.

4. MODIFICATION RIGHTS

   You may modify the Software for your own use. If you distribute 
   modified versions, you must:
   - Clearly indicate that modifications have been made
   - Include a copy of this License
   - Provide attribution to the original project
   - Not use the name "Dome Pro" for modified versions without permission

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

COMMERCIAL USE RESTRICTION

Commercial Use of the Software requires prior written permission from the 
project maintainer.

To obtain commercial use permission, please contact:

    Email: alder.velasquezobando@gmail.com
    Subject: Dome Pro Commercial License Inquiry

Commercial license terms will be discussed on a case-by-case basis. The goal
is to ensure fair use while supporting the sustainability of the project.

Examples of activities that require commercial permission:
- Selling the Software or services based on it
- Using the Software in a paid SaaS offering
- Bundling the Software with commercial products
- Using the Software to provide paid consulting services

Examples of activities that DO NOT require commercial permission:
- Using the Software for personal research
- Using the Software in academic settings
- Internal company use for non-revenue-generating activities (evaluation)
- Contributing improvements back to the project

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SUPPORT AND MAINTENANCE

OFFICIAL SUPPORT

Official support is provided only for the Official Repository. The project 
maintainers are under no obligation to provide support, but community 
assistance is encouraged through:
- GitHub Issues for bug reports and feature requests
- Community discussions for questions and help

NO FORK SUPPORT

We do not provide official support for forks of the Software. If you 
encounter issues with a forked version:
- First, verify the issue exists in the Official Repository
- If unique to your fork, resolve it independently
- Consider contributing any fixes back to the Official Repository

This policy exists to focus our limited resources on improving the main 
project for everyone's benefit.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENTS

When using the Software, you must:

1. Retain all copyright notices and license information
2. Provide visible attribution to Dome Pro in any derivative works
3. Include a link to the Official Repository when reasonable
4. Not imply endorsement by the project maintainers without permission

Suggested attribution format:

    "Built with Dome Pro - https://github.com/[official-repo]"

